Package FitnessClassManager

Class Member

java.lang.Object
FitnessClassManager.Member
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Member>
public class Member extends Object implements Comparable<Member>
Member Class is a blueprint for member objects Stores the following member data: - First and Last name - Date of Birth - Date of Membership Expiration - Location of Gym Membership
Author:
Arya Shetty, John Greaney-Cheng

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Member member)
      Compares the name of this member to another Format: m1.compareTo(m2) First compare last names and if they're the same, compare first names Note: Names are not case-sensitive when compared to one another, all comparisons are done with names converted to lowercase
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Member>
      Parameters:
      member - the member to compare names with (m2)
      Returns:
      >0 if m2's name is greater lexicographically, <0 if m2's name is lesser lexicographically, =0 if m2's name is same as this member

    • callTests

      private static void callTests(String[] m1FirstName, String[] m1LastName, String[] m2FirstName, String[] m2LastName, String expectedResult, int testCase)
      Helper Method for Testbed Main Tests every pair of members individually, outputs if pair PASSed or FAILed expectations m1FirstName[0], m1LastName[0], m2FirstName[0], m2LastName[0], all hold instance variables about the same member pair
      Parameters:
      m1FirstName - array of m1's first name to test
      m1LastName - array of m1's last name to test
      m2FirstName - array of m2's first name to test
      m2LastName - array of m2's last name to test
      expectedResult - expectedResult of the test case
      testCase - the number testcase in the corresponding test design document
